definitions: characterized by or reflecting economy in the use of resources, particularly money
examples: Her frugal lifestyle allowed her to save for retirement
The frugal shopper always compared prices before buying

definitions: producing good or helpful results in abundance; productive and beneficial
examples: Their fruitful collaboration resulted in several patents
The meeting proved fruitful with many new ideas

definitions: producing or capable of producing fruit on a plant or tree
examples: The fruiting branches were heavy with apples
Scientists studied the fruiting patterns of tropical plants

definitions: failing to achieve the desired results; unproductive or pointless in outcome
examples: Their fruitless search lasted for several hours
All attempts to negotiate proved fruitless

definitions: having the taste or smell of fruit, especially when sweet
informal term for eccentric, crazy, or unconventional behavior
examples: The wine had a fruity aroma with hints of berries
This fruity dessert combines mango and passion fruit
His fruity personality made him popular at parties
The comedian's fruity jokes kept everyone laughing

definitions: feeling or expressing distress and annoyance from being unable to achieve something
examples: She felt frustrated by the constant technical problems
The frustrated customers waited in long lines

definitions: causing feelings of anger and annoyance by preventing progress or success
examples: Learning a new language can be frustrating at first
The frustrating delays made everyone late for work

definitions: vulgar slang for being in a very bad or hopeless situation
vulgar slang for being extremely drunk or under influence of drugs
examples: The project is completely fucked without more funding
We're fucked if we miss this deadline
He got so fucked at the party last night
She was too fucked to drive home safely

definitions: supplied with fuel or energy to operate or function
stimulated, intensified, or driven by something that provides motivation
examples: The rocket was fueled and ready for launch
All vehicles must be properly fueled before departure
Her ambition was fueled by early childhood experiences
The debate was fueled by conflicting political views

definitions: British spelling: supplied with fuel or energy to operate
British spelling: stimulated or driven by something providing motivation
examples: The aircraft was fully fuelled for the journey
The generator needs to be fuelled every day
His anger was fuelled by years of injustice
The movement was fuelled by grassroots activism

definitions: describing someone who has escaped and is avoiding capture by authorities
examples: The fugitive suspect was spotted near the border
Police searched for the fugitive prisoner all night

definitions: feeling happy and satisfied with life and achievements
completed or carried out as promised, ordered, or expected
examples: She felt fulfilled in her new career
The artist lived a fulfilled and meaningful life
All orders were fulfilled within two business days
The company fulfilled its contractual obligations

definitions: doing something clumsily or incompetently, especially with the hands
examples: His fumbling attempts to open the lock failed
She made a fumbling search through her purse

definitions: working or operating in a proper and normal way as intended
examples: The hospital has only one functioning elevator
All systems are functioning within normal parameters

definitions: relating to or characteristic of strict adherence to basic principles of a religion or ideology
examples: The fundamentalist preacher rejected modern interpretations
Fundamentalist groups opposed the new legislation

definitions: provided with money for a particular purpose from a source
examples: The research project was funded by government grants
Several funded positions are available this year

definitions: relating to or used for a funeral or the burial of the dead
examples: Ancient funerary rituals were discovered in the tomb
The museum displayed various funerary objects

definitions: of, relating to, or caused by fungi or fungus organisms
examples: The doctor diagnosed a fungal infection
Fungal growth appeared on the damp walls

definitions: having an unconventional style that is fashionable and interesting
having a strong, unpleasant smell, especially musty or moldy
examples: She wore funky vintage clothes to the party
The band played funky jazz fusion music
There's a funky smell coming from the basement
The cheese had a funky odor but tasted great

definitions: extremely angry to the point of rage or losing control
examples: She was furious when she discovered the betrayal
The furious storm caused widespread damage

definitions: equipped with furniture and other necessary items for living or use
examples: The furnished apartment included all basic amenities
They rented a fully furnished vacation home

definitions: covered with fur or a fur-like coating on the surface
examples: The furred animals adapted well to cold climates
His tongue felt furred after the illness

definitions: marked with long narrow grooves or wrinkles, especially on skin
examples: His furrowed brow showed deep concentration
The farmer walked across the furrowed field

definitions: covered with fur or resembling fur in texture or appearance
examples: The furry kitten curled up on the cushion
She wore a furry coat during winter

definitions: at or to a greater distance in space or time
additional or more advanced in degree, extent, or progress
examples: The further shore was barely visible in fog
We need to look further back in history
Further evidence supports the original theory
She had no further questions about the topic

definitions: at or to the greatest distance in space, time, or degree
examples: Neptune is the furthest planet from the sun
This represents the furthest extent of our knowledge

definitions: joined or blended together to form a single entity through heat or chemical process
examples: The metal parts were fused together by welding
The fused glass created beautiful artistic patterns

definitions: incapable of producing any useful result; pointless and doomed to failure
examples: Their futile attempts to save the company failed
Arguing with him about this is completely futile

definitions: relating to futurism or prediction and depiction of the future
examples: The futurist architect designed revolutionary buildings
Futurist predictions often prove surprisingly accurate

definitions: having or involving very modern technology or design seemingly from the future
examples: The car had a sleek futuristic design
The movie depicted a futuristic society

definitions: having a soft, fluffy texture or covered with fine soft hair or fibers
difficult to perceive clearly; indistinct or vague in character
examples: The fuzzy peach skin felt soft to touch
She wore fuzzy slippers around the house
My memories of that day are quite fuzzy
The photograph was too fuzzy to identify faces

definitions: informal term for talking too much, especially about trivial matters
examples: Her gabby neighbor talked for hours about nothing
The gabby salesperson wouldn't stop pitching products

definitions: having one or more gables in architectural design of roofs
examples: The gabled houses lined the historic street
Their gabled roof provided excellent rain drainage

definitions: informal term for being extremely enthusiastic or infatuated with something
informal term for being mentally confused, especially from old age
examples: She went gaga over the new fashion collection
The fans were gaga about their favorite singer
My grandfather is getting a bit gaga these days
The medication made her feel temporarily gaga

definitions: of or relating to a galaxy, especially our Milky Way galaxy
examples: Scientists study galactic formations through powerful telescopes
The movie featured galactic battles between alien races

definitions: brave, heroic, and showing noble qualities in behavior or actions
giving special attention and respect to women in a chivalrous manner
examples: The gallant soldier received medals for bravery
It was a gallant effort despite the failure
He made a gallant gesture by offering his seat
The gallant gentleman helped her with the door

definitions: in abundance or plentiful amounts, always used after the noun
examples: The festival had food and entertainment galore
There were bargains galore at the annual sale

definitions: relating to or involving electric currents produced by chemical action
producing a sudden and dramatic stimulating effect on someone
examples: The scientist studied galvanic reactions in metals
Galvanic corrosion damaged the ship's hull
His speech had a galvanic effect on the crowd
The news produced a galvanic response from investors

definitions: involving the practice of risking money or valuables on games of chance
examples: The city banned gambling establishments downtown
His gambling debts grew larger every month

definitions: wide open, especially referring to holes, wounds, or mouths
examples: A gaping hole appeared in the ship's hull
She stared with gaping mouth at the surprise

definitions: confused, distorted, or meaningless in message or communication
examples: The garbled message was impossible to understand
Radio interference created garbled transmissions

definitions: of enormous size, volume, or degree; gigantic beyond normal proportions
examples: The company faced gargantuan debts after expansion
A gargantuan wave crashed against the lighthouse

definitions: obtrusively bright and showy in a tasteless or vulgar way
examples: The garish neon signs lit up the street
She wore garish makeup that didn't suit her

definitions: existing in the form of gas rather than solid or liquid
examples: Water becomes gaseous when it evaporates
The planet has a thick gaseous atmosphere

definitions: of or relating to the stomach and its functions or diseases
examples: She suffered from severe gastric problems
Gastric juices help digest food in the stomach

definitions: relating to or affecting both the stomach and the intestines in the digestive system
examples: The patient experienced gastrointestinal discomfort after eating
Gastrointestinal diseases require specialized medical treatment

definitions: relating to the art and science of good eating and fine cuisine
examples: Paris offers numerous gastronomic delights for food lovers
The gastronomic festival featured celebrity chefs

definitions: brought together or assembled in one place from various sources
examples: The gathered crowd waited for the announcement
She wore a dress with gathered sleeves

definitions: lacking social grace, sensitivity, or tact; awkward in social situations
examples: His gauche behavior embarrassed everyone at dinner
It would be gauche to mention money now

definitions: extravagantly bright or showy in a tasteless or vulgar way
examples: The gaudy decorations overwhelmed the small room
She avoided wearing gaudy jewelry to work
